casebody.data:
Martha HAGER, Appellant, v. PACIFIC GREYHOUND LINES, INC., a Corporation, Appellee. No. 11229. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 26, 1946. William P. Lord and Ben Anderson, both of Portland, Ore., for appellant. Cooley, Crowley & Supple, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, HEALY, and BONE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the motion of appellant, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be dismissed, without costs to any party, that a judgment he filed and entered accordingly and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
